No, the first "plan" is the xproperties name of the window, which is how
FvwmButtons knows to pop the button back up. At least that's how it's
worked since it was GoodStuff.

Does anyone know how to get that little location button to show up in
the centre of the screen? The one that pops up when you move a window
which shows you the x+y coords? It used to be in the centre of my screen
but since the new version it's showing up in the top left. I can't find
a config option for it.

